    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Sparking Up Kiwi Fruit With a Touch of Gold</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By MELISSA CLARK</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New kiwi fruit cultivar has mustard-hued flesh; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>New Zealand's kiwi growers, seeking to revive the fruit's former glory, have developed a new yellow cultivar. Called a Zespri Gold kiwi, it looks much like the green variety on the outside, but its mustard-hued flesh has a custardy texture and almost melonlike taste. The kiwis are 50 cents each at Gourmet Garage, three for $1.20 at Fairway.</p>
        <p>MELISSA CLARK</p>
      </block>
